%% 3.1.3 Bus Routes — sequence diagram (layered)
%% Actor > UI > Controller > Service > Repository > Database
%% Create path + list refresh; BR03 on delete (implement in BusRouteService — hiện code có thể chưa kiểm tra BR03).

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Actor as Admin or Staff
    participant UI as UI (Bus Routes page)
    participant RC as Controller (BusRouteController)
    participant RS as Service (BusRouteService)
    participant RR as Repository (BusRoute / BusRouteStation)
    participant DB as Database (SQL Server)

    Note over Actor,DB: Page open — fill table
    Actor->>UI: Open Bus Routes from sidebar
    UI->>RC: GET /api/BusRoute/Search (keyword, campusId, paging)
    RC->>RS: SearchBusRouteAsync(...)
    RS->>RR: Query routes + campus + stations
    RR->>DB: EF read
    DB-->>RR: rows
    RR-->>RS: data
    RS-->>RC: PagedResult
    RC-->>UI: 200 + table data

    Note over Actor,DB: Load pickup points for Modal dropdown (Pickup Points module)
    UI->>UI: Open Add Bus Route → Modal + overlay
    UI->>RC: GET /api/BusStation/Search (paging) for station dropdown list
    RC-->>UI: 200 stations for dropdowns

    Note over Actor,DB: Save new route
    Actor->>UI: Fill Name, Code (if any), add stop rows (+), pick stations, Save
    alt Route Name empty (client validation)
        UI->>UI: No HTTP call — red border under Name
        UI-->>Actor: Inline error: Route Name cannot be empty
    else Valid form
        UI->>RC: POST /api/BusRoute/Create (BusRouteCreateDto: Name, CampusId, StationIds)
        RC->>RS: CreateBusRouteAsync(dto)
        RS->>RR: Add BusRoute + BusRouteStation rows
        RR->>DB: INSERT
        DB-->>RR: OK
        RR-->>RS: persisted entity
        RS-->>RC: BusRouteDto
        RC-->>UI: 200 success
        UI->>UI: Close Modal, reload Search, Toast green
        UI-->>Actor: New row visible (e.g. at top)
    end

    Note over Actor,DB: Delete — BR03
    Actor->>UI: Click Delete on a row
    UI->>RC: DELETE /api/BusRoute/Delete/{id}
    RC->>RS: DeleteBusRouteAsync(id)
    RS->>RS: Assert BR03 — no active BusSchedule / assignment using route
    alt BR03 blocks delete
        RS-->>RC: throw (cannot delete)
        RC-->>UI: 400 + message
        UI-->>Actor: Show error — suggest status change only
    else Delete allowed
        RS->>RR: Delete route stations then route
        RR->>DB: DELETE
        DB-->>RR: OK
        RS-->>RC: success
        RC-->>UI: 200
        UI-->>Actor: Table refresh
    end
